<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 11:55PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Hemphill County through 1230 AM CDT...
At 1155 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lake Marvin, or 13 miles east of Canadian. This storm was nearly
stationary.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lake Marvin.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
